A Java-based Passenger Registration System designed to manage passenger details efficiently. This project demonstrates object-oriented programming (OOP), data handling, and input validation by allowing users to register passengers with information like name, age, contact details, and travel data. Ideal for learning practical Java application development.

Features

  Add new passengers with personal and travel details.
  View all registered passengers.
  Update passenger information.
  Input validation to ensure correct and complete data.
  Demonstrates use of classes, objects, and OOP concepts in Java.

Technologies Used

  Java SE
  Object-Oriented Programming
  File handling (optional if storing data in files)
  Console-based user interface

Open the project in your preferred Java IDE (Eclipse, VS Code, NetBeans).
  Compile and run Main.java.
  Usage
  Run the program.

Choose options from the menu:

  Register a new passenger
  View passenger list
  Update passenger details
  view login dasboard
  Logout
